  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to identify risk factors for thromboembolic and /or infectious
      complications in 3,000 patients with solid tumor and receiving a Percutaneous Central Venous
      Catheter (PCVC). A better understanding of the risk factors for these complications in this
      population would then allow interventional studies to be proposed to assess the benefit of
      prophylactic procedures in a sub-group of patients at most risk.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
